ğŸ”¹ 4. Tailwind CSS (Utility-first CSS framework)
Tailwind gives you ready-made CSS utility classes (like bg-blue-500, p-4, text-center) so you donâ€™t write custom CSS much.
Instead of creating CSS files, you apply these classes directly to your JSX elements.

npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
tailwindcss â†’ the framework
postcss â†’ processes Tailwind styles
autoprefixer â†’ adds browser-specific CSS rules automatically

