ğŸ“Œ 6.React Hooks (Core) â€“ Simple Definitions
âœ…1. useState
Lets you add state variables inside functional components.
Example: storing a counter value, input text.
âœ…2. useEffect
Runs side effects after render.
Example: timers, fetching data, subscriptions.
âœ… 3.useRef
Stores a mutable reference that doesnâ€™t re-render the component.
Example: accessing a DOM element or saving a previous value.
âœ…4.useReducer
Alternative to useState for complex state logic.
Uses a reducer function (state, action) â†’ new state.
Example: form validation, counters with multiple actions.
âœ… 5.useContext
Provides a way to share global data between components without passing props manually.
Example: theme, user authentication.

ğŸ“Œ Practical Tasks
Countdown Timer â†’ uses useEffect to decrease time every second.
Theme Switcher â†’ uses useContext to toggle between Light/Dark mode.
Form with Validation â†’ uses useReducer to manage input values and errors.
